---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — \brag pages"
  description="What is a brag page and why you should have one."
>
  <div class="space-y-12">
    <article class="space-y-8">
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="font-display text-zinc-400 text-2xl">What is a /brag page?</h2>
        <p class="w-2/3 leading-relaxed">
          A /brag page is a personal page where you tell people about your professional wins — what
          have you shipped, what are you definitely the best at, what excites you the most about
          your work? <span class="font-semibold">It is an evolving and opinionated record of your career.</span>
        </p>
        <p class="w-2/3 leading-relaxed">This is a collection of all /brag pages submitted by users.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h3 class="font-display text-zinc-400 text-lg">Isn't that what that blue app does?</h3>
        <p class="w-2/3 leading-relaxed">
          Not even close. That app is a platform that owns your data, curates your presentation and
          buries your wins in an algorithm. <span class="font-semibold">A /brag page is yours - your domain, your format, your voice</span>.
          Do it as you please. Share it with us, please.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="space-y-8">
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="font-display text-zinc-400 text-2xl">Who came up with \brag pages?</h2>
        <p class="w-2/3 leading-relaxed">
          <a href="https://x.com/aarondfrancis" target="_blank" class="text-blue-500 border-b border-blue-500">Aaron Francis</a>,
          the 2x dad of twins and father of <a href="https://soloterm.com/" target="_blank" class="text-blue-500 border-b border-blue-500">Solo</a>
          (not a Solo dad though, kudos to Jenifer) and <a href="https://x.com/IanLandsman" target="_blank" class="text-blue-500 border-b border-blue-500">Ian Landsman</a>,
          The Business Dad, initiated the talks about brag pages on episode 132 of The Mostly Technical Podcast.
        </p>
        <div>
          <a href="/submit" class="text-blue-500 border-b border-blue-500 w-fit">Listen to Mostly Technical Podcast</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h3 class="font-display text-zinc-400 text-lg">Who built this website?</h3>
        <p class="w-2/3 leading-relaxed">
          This website was built by <a href="https://x.com/amarelodandara" target="_blank" class="text-blue-500 border-b border-blue-500">Dandara</a>,
          a <span class="italic">mostly technical</span> designer.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
          <a href="https://adandara.com" target="_blank" class="text-blue-500 border-b border-blue-500 w-fit">Check out her portfolio</a>
          <a href="https://adandara.com/building-a-home-for-braggers" target="_blank" class="text-blue-500 border-b border-blue-500 w-fit">Read more about this website development</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="space-y-8">
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="font-display text-zinc-400 text-2xl">How to submit a /brag page?</h2>
        <p class="w-2/3 leading-relaxed">
          Open a pull request on the GitHub repo and add your entry to <code>brags.json</code>. The
          <a href="/submit" class="text-blue-500 border-b border-blue-500">submit page</a> has all the details.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h3 class="font-display text-zinc-400 text-lg">How to remove my page from the list?</h3>
        <p class="w-2/3 leading-relaxed">
          To remove your page from the list, simply <a href="https://github.com/nydndr/brag/issues/new" target="_blank" class="text-blue-500 border-b border-blue-500">open an issue on GitHub</a>
          or better yet open a PR removing your entry from the data file.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="space-y-8">
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="font-display text-zinc-400 text-2xl">How does this website work?</h2>
        <p class="w-2/3 leading-relaxed">
          I could tell you, but better yet, I could show you! It is open source, have a blast digging
          the <a href="https://github.com/nydndr/brag" target="_blank" class="text-blue-500 border-b border-blue-500">code on GitHub</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>

    <article class="space-y-8">
      <div class="space-y-2">
        <h2 class="font-display text-zinc-400 text-2xl">So... I have a suggestion!</h2>
        <p class="w-2/3 leading-relaxed">
          That's awesome! You can either open an issue - or better yet, a PR - on <a href="https://github.com/nydndr/brag" target="_blank" class="text-blue-500 border-b border-blue-500">GitHub</a>
          or @ me on <a href="https://X.com/amarelodandara" target="_blank" class="text-blue-500 border-b border-blue-500">Twitter (@amarelodandara)</a>,
          the everything app.
        </p>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
